home.startDescription: Participate in the development of your own community

youthcouncil2015.pfblockSubtitle: Local youth councils are forums that represent the views of young people at a local level. Run by young people for young people, they give young people a voice and enable them to make their views heard in the decision-making process. They give young people the chance to discuss relevant issues, engage with decision makers and contribute to improving the lives of young people within their communities.
youthcouncil2015.iconboxDesc1: Choose your town and join a motivated team...
youthcouncil2015.iconboxDesc2: The 6 Local youth councils are: Cite El-Riadh, Kalaa Kebira, Ksibet Mediouni, M'Saken, Hammam sousse and Sousse.
youthcouncil2015.iconboxDesc3: We have at least 1 project in each town.
